event_narrative:
Once the program was put on a sound foundation for development through launch with the JWST rebaseline in 2011, NASA had to address the management issues identified by the independent review panel. The new JWST Program Director describes changes in five areas that have led, thus far, to considerably improved telescope development performance. The areas are:

  clearly defined authority, responsibility and accountability;  
  improved communication;  
  commitment to the established baseline;  
  improved risk management;  
  independent review and increased program planning and control capability and analysis.  
</ul>
